; Re-templated zone file -- what a SUBSEQUENT deployment writes over the
; existing file.  Two things mirror the real bodsch.dns.bind behaviour:
;
;   1. A fresh, much higher "epoch" serial (2000000000) that does NOT appear
;      anywhere in the leftover journal's transaction range.  The role mints
;      int(time.time()) whenever it cannot find its own "; Hash:" marker -- and
;      that marker is gone because named rewrote the file during the dynamic
;      update.
;   2. The dynamically-added record is absent (the template only knows about
;      statically-declared hosts).
;
; On the next named start, BIND tries to roll the stale journal forward onto
; this file, the serials do not line up, and it refuses to load the zone:
;   "journal rollforward failed: journal out of sync with zone".
;
; Copyright 2026 Buo-ren Lin (OSSII) <buoren.lin@ossii.com.tw>
; SPDX-License-Identifier: AGPL-3.0-or-later
$TTL 600
@   IN SOA ns.repro.test. admin.repro.test. (
            2000000000 ; serial  (fresh epoch, disjoint from the journal)
            60         ; refresh
            60         ; retry
            604800     ; expire
            10 )       ; minimum
    IN NS  ns.repro.test.
ns  IN A   127.0.0.1
